I ignored the idea that I was telling an actual human friend who had fallen asleep and I imagined that it was a sketch artist or a computer friend. This made it easier to justify the level of detail that was needed for the task. I tried to repeat the film dialogue in my head as it happened in the movie. I tried to focus more on the audio than I did the visual elements. I tried to put a name to a face as early as I could to make it easier to think of them as important rather than a background character. I made sure to keep a running timeline in my head and connect the characters across scene changes. In my recalls, I tried not to use the character's name until I was describing the part where it was given. This helped me relive the recall more accurately, I believe.
